er","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50},{"title":"Brillouin Scattering","href":"/materials/brillouin-scattering","description":"Stimulated Brillouin scattering (SBS): frequency shift, gain coefficient, and power threshold in optical fibers and bulk materials.","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","brillouin-scattering","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Calcite (CaCO₃) Properties","href":"/materials/calcite-properties","description":"Uniaxial negative crystal with the largest birefringence of common optical crystals. Δn ≈ 0.172 at 589nm.","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","calcite-properties","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Carrier-Envelope Phase (CEP)","href":"/wave-optics/cep-stabilization","description":"CEP offset effects on few-cycle pulse electric field.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","cep-stabilization","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"CARS Imaging Calculator","href":"/imaging/coherent-anti-stokes","description":"Coherent Anti-Stokes Raman Scattering: vibrational shift, CARS wavelength, and laser parameters.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","coherent-anti-stokes","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cavity Mode Spacing","href":"/wave-optics/cavity-mode-spacing","description":"Axial and transverse mode structure of optical resonators.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","cavity-mode-spacing","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cavity Ring-Down Spectroscopy","href":"/spectroscopy/cavity-ring-down","description":"Model CRDS ring-down time, sensitivity, and finesse. Visualize exponential decay with and without sample absorption.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","cavity-ring-down","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cavity Stability Diagram","href":"/wave-optics/cavity-stability","description":"Two-mirror cavity stability: g₁ = 1 - L/R₁, g₂ = 1 - L/R₂. Stable when 0 ≤ g₁g₂ ≤ 1.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","cavity-stability","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cavity-Dumped Laser","href":"/wave-optics/cavity-dumped","description":"Energy extraction from a laser cavity using fast Q-switching or intracavity modulation.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","cavity-dumped","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"CCD vs CMOS Comparison","href":"/detectors/ccd-cmos","description":"Compare SNR and dynamic range between CCD and CMOS detectors.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","ccd-cmos","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"CCD vs CMOS Sensor Comparison","href":"/detectors/ccd-vs-cmos","description":"Compare sensor architectures — SNR, dynamic range, and performance metrics.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","ccd-vs-cmos","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"CCD/CCM Sensor Design","href":"/imaging/sensor-ccm","description":"CCD sensor parameters, cooling requirements, dark current, and dynamic range analysis.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","sensor-ccm","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Chalcogenide Glass Properties","href":"/materials/chalcogenide-glass","description":"IR-transparent glasses for thermal imaging, sensing, and nonlinear optics","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","chalcogenide-glass","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Channel Capacity","href":"/free-space-comms/channel-capacity","description":"Open Channel Capacity.","kind":"page","category":"free-space-comms","tags":["free-space-comms","channel-capacity","fso","link budget","fog","scintillation","pointing"],"priority":50},{"title":"Channel Photomultiplier (Multi-Channel PMT)","href":"/detectors/channel-photomultiplier","description":"Multi-channel PMT: gain staging, energy resolution, and timing.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","channel-photomultiplier","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"Chirped Pulse Amplification (CPA)","href":"/wave-optics/chirped-pulse","description":"Stretch, amplify, compress — bypassing damage thresholds.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","chirped-pulse","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"Chromatic Dispersion","href":"/materials/chromatic-dispersion","description":"Material dispersion dn/dλ from Sellmeier coefficients","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","chromatic-dispersion","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Chromatic Dispersion (CD)","href":"/fiber-optics/chromatic-dispersion","description":"Calculate chromatic dispersion, pulse broadening, and system penalties for single-mode fiber.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","chromatic-dispersion","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Circular Dichroism","href":"/polarization/circular-dichroism","description":"Calculate CD parameters: ΔA, Δε, molar ellipticity, and g-factor from absorbance of left and right circularly polarized light.","kind":"page","category":"polarization","tags":["polarization","circular-dichroism","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cleared Tissue Imaging Calculator","href":"/imaging/cleared-tissue","description":"Optical clearing tissue imaging: resolution, transmission, ballistic photon fraction, and RI matching.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","cleared-tissue","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"CMOS Sensor Design","href":"/imaging/sensor-cmos","description":"Pixel design parameters, dynamic range, noise floor, and sensitivity calculations.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","sensor-cmos","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coating Stress & Curvature","href":"/thin-film/stress","description":"Stoney's equation: σ = E·ts²/(6·R·tf). Relates film stress to substrate curvature.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","stress","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coating Stress &amp; Curvature","href":"/thin-film/coating-stress","description":"Stoney equation: κ = 6σfdf / (Ests²). Relates thin-film stress to substrate curvature. Valid for thin films (df ≪ ts).","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","coating-stress","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coefficient of Thermal Expansion","href":"/materials/coefficient-thermal-expansion","description":"Thermal expansion of optical materials","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","coefficient-thermal-expansion","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coherent Anti-Stokes Raman Scattering (CARS)","href":"/spectroscopy/coherent-anti-stokes-raman","description":"Four-wave mixing process for label-free vibrational imaging with chemical specificity.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","coherent-anti-stokes-raman","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coherent Anti-Stokes Raman Spectroscopy (CARS)","href":"/spectroscopy/coherent-anti-stokes","description":"Four-wave mixing process: ω_CARS = ω_pump − ω_Stokes + ω_probe. Coherent, directional signal above fluorescence.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","coherent-anti-stokes","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coherent Raman (CARS/SRS) Calculator","href":"/imaging/coherent-raman","description":"Coherent Anti-Stokes Raman Scattering and Stimulated Raman Scattering signal estimation.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","coherent-raman","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coherent Raman Microscopy Calculator","href":"/imaging/coherent-raman-microscopy","description":"Calculate Stokes wavelengths, spectral resolution, and spatial resolution for CARS and SRS microscopy.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","coherent-raman-microscopy","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cold Mirror Design","href":"/thin-film/cold-mirror","description":"Cold mirrors reflect visible light while transmitting infrared. Used in projector systems, illumination optics, and laser setups to separate visible from IR (heat). The (HL)N stack is a high-reflector centered in the visible band, while IR passes through the stop band edges.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","cold-mirror","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Color Centers in Crystals","href":"/materials/color-centers","description":"Point defects and impurity centers: absorption/emission spectra, cross-sections, and ZPL characteristics. Key for quantum emitters and tunable lasers.","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","color-centers","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Computational Imaging","href":"/imaging/computational-imaging","description":"Multi-view fusion, resolution scaling, and SNR improvement 