nt parameters and build link budgets for different connector types.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","connector-insertion-loss","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Connector Return Loss","href":"/fiber-optics/connector-return","description":"Calculates return loss (RL) and insertion loss (IL) for fiber connectors with air gaps, lateral offsets, and angular misalignment. Fresnel: r = (n₁ − n₂)/(n₁ + n₂), RL = −20 log₁₀|r|. Physical contact (PC) eliminates air gap.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","connector-return","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Connector Return Loss","href":"/fiber-optics/connector-return-loss","description":"Calculate return loss (ORL) from fiber connectors based on polish type and index mismatch.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","connector-return-loss","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Conoscopic Observation","href":"/polarization/conoscopic","description":"Simulate conoscopic interference figures (isochromates and isogyres) for uniaxial and biaxial crystals between crossed polarizers.","kind":"page","category":"polarization","tags":["polarization","conoscopic","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50},{"title":"Contamination Effects","href":"/materials/contamination","description":"Particle contamination impact on optical surfaces","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","contamination","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cooling Benefit Calculator","href":"/detectors/cooling-benefit","description":"Dark current reduction and SNR improvement from thermoelectric (TEC) or cryogenic cooling.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","cooling-benefit","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"Corneal Exposure Limits","href":"/laser-safety/corneal-limits","description":"Corneal MPE across UV, visible, and IR spectral regions. Simplified model.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","corneal-limits","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"Corneal vs Retinal Limits","href":"/laser-safety/corneal-vs-retinal","description":"Compares corneal MPE with equivalent retinal irradiance, showing the eye&apos;s focusing gain and which limit governs.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","corneal-vs-retinal","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"Cosmic Ray Detection","href":"/detectors/cosmic-rays","description":"Cosmic ray flux and impact on imaging sensors — estimate hit rates and affected pixels.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","cosmic-rays","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"Coupled Mode Theory","href":"/wave-optics/coupled-mode","description":"Power exchange between two coupled waveguides.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","coupled-mode","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"Crystal Birefringence Data","href":"/materials/crystal-birefringence","description":"Δn = |nₒ − nₑ| for uniaxial and birefringent crystals at selected wavelength","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","crystal-birefringence","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"D-Shaped Fiber","href":"/fiber-optics/d-shaped-fiber","description":"Birefringence, evanescent field, and polarization properties of D-shaped (flat) fibers.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","d-shaped-fiber","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Dark Current vs Temperature","href":"/detectors/dark-current","d