cence Quantum Yield","href":"/spectroscopy/fluorescence-quantum-yield","description":"Φ = Φ_ref · (I_s/I_ref) · (A_ref/A_s) · (n_s/n_ref)² — comparative method using a reference standard.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","fluorescence-quantum-yield","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Fluorescence Spectra Overlap Calculator","href":"/imaging/fluorescence-spectra","description":"Compare excitation/emission spectra, spectral overlap, and filter crosstalk.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","fluorescence-spectra","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Fluoride Glass (ZBLAN)","href":"/materials/fluoride-glass","description":"Heavy-metal fluoride glasses for mid-IR fiber optics and low-loss transmission","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","fluoride-glass","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Fog Attenuation","href":"/free-space-comms/fog-attenuation","description":"Open Fog Attenuation.","kind":"page","category":"free-space-comms","tags":["free-space-comms","fog-attenuation","fso","link budget","fog","scintillation","pointing"],"priority":50},{"title":"Four-Wave Mixing (FWM)","href":"/wave-optics/four-wave-mixing","description":"Degenerate FWM with energy conservation 2ωp = ωs + ωi in fibers and waveguides.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","four-wave-mixing","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"Fourier Self-Comb Spectroscopy","href":"/spectroscopy/fourier-self-comb","description":"Optical frequency comb from a single microresonator. Dual-comb spectroscopy without two separate lasers.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","fourier-self-comb","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Fourier Transform Basics","href":"/spectrosco