an Spectroscopy (SERS)","href":"/spectroscopy/surface-enhanced-raman","description":"EM and chemical enhancement mechanisms, hotspots, and detection limit estimation.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","surface-enhanced-raman","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Tapered Fiber Design","href":"/fiber-optics/tapered-fiber","description":"Design adiabatic fiber tapers for mode conversion, evanescent field enhancement, and coupler fabrication.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","tapered-fiber","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Telecentric Lens Design","href":"/imaging/telecentricity","description":"Telecentric lenses maintain constant magnification regardless of object distance. Chief rays are parallel to optical axis.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","telecentricity","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Temporal Noise","href":"/detectors/temporal-noise","description":"1/f noise, white (shot) noise, and read noise as functions of frequency and integration time.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","temporal-noise","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"Terahertz (THz) Spectroscopy","href":"/spectroscopy/terahertz-spectroscopy","description":"Probing low-energy excitations: phonon modes, hydrogen bonding, lattice vibrations (0.1–10 THz).","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","terahertz-spectroscopy","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thermal Conductivity for Optics","href":"/materials/thermal-conductivity-optics","description":"Heat transport in optical substrates","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","thermal-conductivity-optics","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thermal Evaporation","href":"/thin-film/thermal-evaporation","description":"Model thermal evaporation: vapor pressure, deposition rate, mean free path, and film uniformity using Hertz-Knudsen and Clausius-Clapeyron equations.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","thermal-evaporation","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thermal Expansion","href":"/materials/thermal-expansion","description":"ΔL = α · ΔT · L — dimensional change from temperature","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","thermal-expansion","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thermal Lens Hazard","href":"/laser-safety/thermal-lens-hazard","description":"Evaluate thermal lensing risk to protective eyewear and optical components from absorbed laser power.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","thermal-lens-hazard","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thermal vs Photochemical MPE","href":"/laser-safety/thermal-vs-photochemical","description":"Compare thermal and photochemical MPE limits — the more restrictive applies.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","thermal-vs-photochemical","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thermo-Optic Coefficient (dn/dT)","href":"/materials/thermal-dndt","description":"Temperature-dependent refractive index change. Positive dn/dT means n increases with temperature.","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","thermal-dndt","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thin Disk Laser","href":"/wave-optics/thin-disk-laser","description":"Open Thin Disk Laser.","kind":"page","category":"wave-optics","tags":["wave-optics","thin-disk-laser","gaussian beam","abcd","cavity","mode matching","diffraction"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thin Film Interference Conditions","href":"/thin-film/interference-conditions","description":"Constructive and destructive interference patterns from a single thin film, accounting for phase shifts at boundaries.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","interference-conditions","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thin Film Stress Measurement","href":"/thin-film/stress-measurement","description":"Calculate film stress from substrate curvature using the Stoney equation. Includes thermal stress decomposition and stored elastic energy.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","stress-measurement","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Thin Lens Image Distance","href":"/imaging/image-distance","description":"Calculate image distance, magnification, and conjugate ratio for a thin lens.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","image-distance","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Third Harmonic Generation (THG) Calculator","href":"/imaging/third-harmonic-generation","description":"THG imaging parameters for interface and membrane contrast in biological samples.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","third-harmonic-generation","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Third-Harmonic Generation Microscopy Calculator","href":"/imaging/third-harmonic-microscopy","description":"Calculate THG wavelength, signal intensity, and resolution for label-free interface and heterogeneity imaging.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","third-harmonic-microscopy","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Three-Photon Microscopy Calculator","href":"/imaging/three-photon-microscopy","description":"Calculate resolution, excitation volume, and depth penetration for three-photon excitation microscopy at 1300+ nm.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","three-photon-microscopy","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Time-Resolved Spectroscopy","href":"/spectroscopy/time-resolved","description":"TCSPC and streak camera fundamentals. IRF convolution, temporal resolution, and decay analysis.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","time-resolved","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"TIRF Penetration Depth Calculator","href":"/imaging/tirf","description":"Evanescent field penetration depth for Total Internal Reflection Fluorescence microscopy.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","tirf","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Total Magnification Calculator","href":"/imaging/magnification","description":"Calculate total system magnification from objective, tube lens, and camera adapter lens.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","magnification","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Transient Absorption Spectroscopy","href":"/spectroscopy/transient-absorption","description":"ΔA spectra vs delay time. Decompose into GSB, ESA, and SE contributions across the probe range.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","transient-absorption","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Transparency Range","href":"/materials/transparency-range","description":"UV cutoff to IR cutoff for common optical materials","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","transparency-range","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Dimensional (2D) Spectroscopy","href":"/spectroscopy/two-dimensional","description":"Correlates excitation and detection frequencies via three-pulse photon echo. Reveals coupling, energy transfer, and homogeneous vs inhomogeneous broadening.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","two-dimensional","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Layer AR Coating","href":"/thin-film/double-layer-ar","description":"Transfer-matrix method for two-layer V-coat or W-coat AR designs. Both layers at quarter-wave optical thickness. Optimal indices: n₁ = (ninc³ · nsub)¼, n₂ = (ninc · nsub³)¼.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","double-layer-ar","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Layer AR Coating","href":"/thin-film/multilayer-ar","description":"Design a two-layer anti-reflection coating. Optimal condition: n₂ = n₁√nsub.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","multilayer-ar","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Photon Absorption","href":"/materials/two-photon-absorption","description":"Nonlinear absorption coefficient β₂PA and intensity-dependent transmission. TPA becomes significant at high peak intensities (pulsed lasers).","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","two-photon-absorption","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Photon Excitation Calculator","href":"/imaging/two-photon-excitation","description":"Calculate two-photon excitation wavelength, peak power, and pulse energy from laser parameters.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","two-photon-excitation","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Photon Microscopy Calculator","href":"/imaging/two-photon","description":"Excitation wavelength, resolution, and pulse parameters for two-photon fluorescence microscopy.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","two-photon","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Two-Photon Microscopy Calculator","href":"/imaging/two-photon-microscopy","description":"Calculate resolution, excitation volume, peak intensity, and depth penetration for two-photon fluorescence microscopy.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","two-photon-microscopy","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Ultrafast Laser Safety Calculator","href":"/laser-safety/ultrafast-laser-safety","description":"Evaluate single-pulse, average-power, and PRF-corrected MPE for femtosecond/picosecond laser systems.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","ultrafast-laser-safety","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"UV / Blue Light Hazard","href":"/laser-safety/uv-blue-hazard","description":"Calculates weighted hazard using the blue light B(λ) and UV S(λ) action spectra per IEC 62471 / ICNIRP guidelines.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","uv-blue-hazard","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"UV Blocking Filter","href":"/thin-film/uv-blocking","description":"Quarter-wave stack designed to reflect UV (200–400 nm) while transmitting visible light.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","uv-blocking","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"UV Exposure Limits","href":"/laser-safety/uv-exposure","description":"Calculate UV exposure limits based on ICNIRP/ACGIH actinic UV weighting for 180–400 nm.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","uv-exposure","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"UV Hazard Calculator","href":"/laser-safety/uv-hazard","description":"UV hazard assessment using ACGIH actinic UV weighting function S(λ). Covers 200–400 nm spectral region.","kind":"page","category":"laser-safety","tags":["laser-safety","uv-hazard","laser safety","mpe","nohd","od","eyewear","hazard"],"priority":50},{"title":"UV Optical Materials","href":"/materials/uv-materials","description":"Deep UV to near-UV materials comparison. Sellmeier: n² = 1 + Σ Biλ²/(λ² - Ci)","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","uv-materials","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"V Number","href":"/fiber-optics/v-number","description":"Open V Number.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","v-number","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Vacuum Photodiode","href":"/detectors/vacuum-photodiode","description":"Vacuum photodiode calculator. Models photoemission, responsivity, dark current (thermionic emission), and frequency response.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","vacuum-photodiode","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"Verdet Constant","href":"/materials/verdet-constant","description":"Faraday rotation: θ = V · B · L, where V ∝ 1/λ² for paramagnetic materials","kind":"page","category":"materials","tags":["materials","verdet-constant","sellmeier","dispersion","glass","index","material properties"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wavefront Error Analysis","href":"/imaging/wavefront-error","description":"Analyze wavefront error in waves RMS, compute Strehl ratio, and check diffraction-limited condition.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","wavefront-error","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wavefront Sensing","href":"/imaging/wavefront-sensing","description":"Wavefront error analysis, Zernike decomposition, Strehl ratio, and sensor sensitivity.","kind":"page","category":"imaging","tags":["imaging","wavefront-sensing","resolution","na","microscopy","airy","mtf","psf"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wavelength Selection","href":"/free-space-comms/wavelength-selection","description":"Open Wavelength Selection.","kind":"page","category":"free-space-comms","tags":["free-space-comms","wavelength-selection","fso","link budget","fog","scintillation","pointing"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wavelength Separation","href":"/thin-film/wavelength-separation","description":"Wavelength separation coatings combine multiple quarter-wave stacks at different design wavelengths to reflect specific bands while transmitting others. Two stacks centered at λ₁ and λ₂ = 1.25·λ₁ demonstrate dichroic behavior. The combined stack shows how reflectance bands add when cascaded.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","wavelength-separation","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wavelength-Dependent Attenuation","href":"/fiber-optics/attenuation","description":"Fiber attenuation spectrum showing Rayleigh scattering, IR absorption, and OH peak for standard fiber types.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","attenuation","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wavenumber Converter","href":"/spectroscopy/wavenumber-converter","description":"Convert wavelength, wavenumber, frequency, and energy with sliders, presets, and range sweeps.","kind":"page","category":"spectroscopy","tags":["spectroscopy","wavenumber-converter","beer lambert","ftir","blackbody","raman","wavenumber"],"priority":50},{"title":"Waveplate / Retarder","href":"/polarization/retarder","description":"Polarization state transformation by a birefringent waveplate with variable retardance and fast-axis orientation.","kind":"page","category":"polarization","tags":["polarization","retarder","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50},{"title":"Waveplate Order","href":"/polarization/waveplate-order","description":"Calculate waveplate order, retardation, and wavelength-dependent performance.","kind":"page","category":"polarization","tags":["polarization","waveplate-order","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50},{"title":"Waveplate Thickness Calculator","href":"/polarization/waveplate-thickness","description":"Calculate required crystal thickness for waveplates of any retardance order.","kind":"page","category":"polarization","tags":["polarization","waveplate-thickness","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wdm Coupler","href":"/fiber-optics/wdm-coupler","description":"Open Wdm Coupler.","kind":"page","category":"fiber-optics","tags":["fiber-optics","wdm-coupler","fiber","mfd","na","dispersion","splice","coupling"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wedge Thin Film","href":"/thin-film/wedge-film","description":"Wedged thin films have a linearly varying thickness across the surface, creating spatially varying interference. Used in optical testing (Newton&apos;s rings, Fizeau interferometry), anti-reflection edge filters, and precision thickness measurement. The fringe spacing Δx = λ / (2n·tan α) determines the spatial period of constructive interference.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","wedge-film","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Well Capacity & Dynamic Range","href":"/detectors/well-capacity","description":"DR = 20·log₁₀(Nwell/σread). C = Nwell·q/Vswing. Larger wells → more DR but slower charge transfer.","kind":"page","category":"detectors","tags":["detectors","well-capacity","sensor","noise","qe","responsivity","nep","detectivity"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wide Bandpass Filter","href":"/thin-film/wide-bandpass","description":"Cascaded short-pass + long-pass quarter-wave stacks for broad transmission bands.","kind":"page","category":"thin-film","tags":["thin-film","wide-bandpass","coating","ar","dielectric stack","bragg","reflectance"],"priority":50},{"title":"Wire Grid Polarizer Calculator","href":"/polarization/wire-grid","description":"Model wire grid polarizers — metallic wires on a substrate that reflect E∥ and transmit E⊥.","kind":"page","category":"polarization","tags":["polarization","wire-grid","stokes","jones","mueller","waveplate","polarizer"],"priority":50}